I believe finding that balance between virtual and in-person connections is key. Personally, I've found that making the effort to meet up with friends face-to-face, even if it's just for a quick coffee, can really make a difference in how connected and supported I feel. It's all about quality over quantity when it comes to combating loneliness, I guess.
